reachabilityData.publicComment: fs_events depends on code from url https://fsevents-binaries.s3-us-west-2.amazonaws.com, which at some point have been controlled by a malicious actor. It's no longer the case and the vulnerability is thus no longer relevant, but it's possible that you may previously have been exposed to the vulnerable artifact.
MongoDB does not adequately handle exceptions when a collection name is invalid and the database does not exist, leading to the application crashing.
A carefully crafted request to the websocket server can cause denial of service due to this ReDoS vulnerability.
